PART 2
1 Section 2.2005. To the Department of Elementary and Secondary
2 Education
3 In reference to all sections in Part 1 of this act:
4 No funds shall be expended for personal service from any line
5 unless said line explicitly states that the purpose of the
6 appropriation includes either “Personal Service” or “All
7 Expenditures.”
1 Section 2.2010. To the Department of Elementary and Secondary
2 Education

HCS HB 2002 29
3 In reference to Section 2.335 and Section 2.340 of Part 1 of this
4 act:
5 No funds shall be expended in furtherance of provider
6 reimbursement rates greater than the 100th percentile of the
7 current child care market for infant and toddler provider rates, as
8 determined by the 2024 child care market rate survey, and no
9 funds shall be expended in furtherance of provider
10 reimbursement rates greater than the 65th percentile of the
11 current child care market for pre-kindergarten and school-age
12 provider rates, as determined by the 2024 child care market rate
13 survey.
14 The Department shall require rate documentation from all
15 providers sufficient to validate reported rates in the 2024 child
16 care market rate study and shall not rely solely upon unaudited
17 self-reported survey responses.
18 The Department shall not hold providers harmless from rate
19 reductions when setting rates. Provider reimbursement rates paid
20 from funds appropriated in these sections shall be reflective
21 solely of rates supported by the 2024 child care market rate
22 survey and shall not exceed the applicable percentile limitations
23 stated herein.
24 No funds appropriated in these sections shall be expended for rate
25 enhancements, beyond the base provider reimbursement rate
26 supported by the 2024 child care market rate survey.
27 Payments to providers shall be based solely on a child’s actual
28 attendance and shall not be made prospectively, on authorization,
29 enrollment, contracted slots, or any other non-attendance-based
30 methodology.
31 No funds shall be expended in furtherance of any benefit greater
32 than that provided for by the applicable traditional or transitional
33 child care subsidy income eligibility threshold.
